# Installation Guide

This project requires **Python**, **Ollama**, and the **Qwen models** to run the vision-language code extraction pipeline.

---

# 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/shasank-shah/LJMU_THESIS.git
cd LJMU_THESIS
```

---

# 2. Install Python Dependencies

Install the required Python libraries using `requirements.txt`.

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### requirements.txt

```txt
requests>=2.31.0
```

---

# 3. Install Ollama

Ollama is required to run the **Qwen Vision-Language and Code models locally**.

## macOS

Using Homebrew:

```bash
brew install ollama
```

Or using the official install script:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh
```

---

## Linux

Install using the official script:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh
```

---

## Windows

Install using **winget**:

```powershell
winget install Ollama.Ollama
```

Or download the installer from:

https://ollama.com/download

---

# 4. Start Ollama

After installation, start the Ollama service:

```bash
ollama serve
```

---

# 5. Download Required Models

Pull the required **Qwen models** used in the pipeline.

```bash
ollama pull qwen2.5vl:latest
ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:7b
```

These models are used as:

| Model         | Purpose                                               |
| ------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| qwen2.5vl     | Vision-Language model for extracting code from images |
| qwen2.5-coder | Code model for reconstruction and correction          |

---

# 6. Verify Installation

Check that Ollama and models are available:

```bash
ollama list
```

Expected output should include:

```
qwen2.5vl
qwen2.5-coder
```

---

# 7. Run the Pipeline

Example command:

```bash
python thesis_img_to_code_pipeline.py \
--dataset_dir dataset \
--out_dir outputs \
--exp E4 \
--generate_code \
--vision_model qwen2.5vl:latest \
--coder_model qwen2.5-coder:7b \
--max_retries 2 \
--timeout_s 900 \
--ollama_bin "/usr/local/bin/ollama"
```

---

